HEADWORD: Bezonian
<hw>Be*zo"ni*an</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>besoin</ets> need, want, It <ets>bisogno</ets>.]</ety> <def>A low
fellow or scoundrel; a beggar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Great men oft die by vile <qex>bezonians</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

